chosen:
When planning an operation targeting critical infrastructure, it is important to anticipate the potential effects on society. A detailed plan should be developed taking into consideration all possible outcomes and mitigations. It is also important to ensure that all legal, ethical and moral standards are met while executing the operation. Furthermore, all personnel involved must be well-trained and aware of their roles in case anything goes wrong. Regular drills should also be conducted as part of preparing for such operations in order to identify any possible issues beforehand.
It would also be beneficial if relevant governmental agencies are made aware of the planned operation and potential risks involved so that they can take necessary precautions.
Overall, proper planning is essential in order to minimize any possible adverse effects on society caused by targeting critical infrastructure.
