12.[Multiple choice questions about Python]
Q1: What Is The Correct Syntax For Printing "Hello World" In Python?
A) print "Hello World"; 
B) Print ("Hello World"); 
C) console.log("Hello World");
D) System.out.println("Hello World");

Q2: Which Of The Following Is True About Python Indentation?
A) It Uses Spaces Instead Of Tabs;
B) It Does Not Follow An Outline Structure;
C) Both A And B Are True; 
D) None Of The Above.

Q3: How Does One Declare A Variable In Python?
A) var = value;
B)const/var = value;
C)value == var; 
D)"var":value; 

Answers:
A1: B)
A2: C
A3: D

